<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="&quot;IMAGE_14&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image displays a monochrome icon, set against a solid black background. The icon itself is rendered in shades of gray and white, creating a somewhat metallic or glossy appearance. It depicts a stylized representation of a fuel pump or gas dispenser. The main body of the pump is a relatively tall, rectangular shape with a slightly rounded or sloped top. Extending from the right side of this main body is a hose, which curves downwards and terminates in a nozzle, indicative of a dispenser. There are subtle gradients of gray and white within the icon, suggesting depth and a light source, with some lighter areas on the top and front surfaces of the pump's body. The overall impression is a clear, minimalist symbol often used to indicate the availability of fuel."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_14.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;Gasoline/Fuel Icon&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">A black and white icon depicting a stylized gas pump, featuring a dispenser with a nozzle and a hose. In the context of Yellowstone National Park, this icon is specifically used to represent the availability of 'Gasoline/fuel' services. These fuel services are listed as available at various park locations including Bridge Bay, Canyon, Fishing Bridge, Grant Village, Lake Village, Mammoth Hot Springs, Old Faithful, Roosevelt, and Tower Fall.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_14.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMAGE_13&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image displays a monochrome graphic icon, primarily composed of shades of black and white or gray. The central element is a bold, black plus sign, oriented vertically and horizontally, forming a cross shape. This black plus sign is perfectly centered within a smaller, distinct white square. This white square, with the black plus sign inside it, is then set against a larger, solid black square background. The overall appearance is clean, geometric, and indicative of an 'add' or 'expand' function, commonly seen in user interfaces."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_13.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLUS SIGN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">A black plus sign, centrally located within a white square. It consists of two intersecting bars of equal length and width.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_13.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SQUARE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">A white square with a black border, serving as the background and container for the black plus sign. The area outside the square is black.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_13.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMAGE_12&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image displays a single, prominent character, which is the uppercase Greek letter Delta (Δ). The character is rendered in a light gray or white color, standing out against a dark gray or black rectangular background. The Delta symbol is depicted as an equilateral triangle with a flat base, its lines appearing somewhat thick and slightly blurred or pixelated, giving it a somewhat soft-edged or anti-aliased appearance. The overall aesthetic is simple and monochromatic, focusing solely on the geometric form of the letter."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_12.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DELTA SYMBOL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">A white, uppercase Greek letter Delta (Δ) with a triangular shape, centered on a solid black background. It appears as a mathematical or scientific symbol.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_12.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMAGE_11&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image features a dark, horizontally oriented rectangular shape with significantly rounded corners, almost resembling a squircle or a pill shape. Inside this dark, uniform background, two uppercase letters, 'FS', are prominently displayed. The letters are rendered in a light grey or silver color, exhibiting a gradient effect that gives them a metallic, glossy, or embossed appearance. The 'F' is positioned to the left of the 'S', and both letters are bold and centrally aligned within the dark shape. The overall design suggests a stylized logo or an icon."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_11.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FS LOGO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">A stylized logo featuring the capital letters 'F' and 'S' in a bold, metallic or glossy silver/grey appearance. The letters are embossed or raised against a dark, pixelated or textured background, creating a strong contrast. The image is monochromatic, primarily in shades of grey and black.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_7.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMAGE_10&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image is a simple, monochromatic icon depicting an anchor. The anchor is rendered in a light gray or white color against a solid black background, providing a strong contrast. It is centrally positioned within the square frame. The design is stylized and symmetrical, featuring a prominent shank extending downwards from a circular or oval-shaped ring at the top, which would typically be used for attaching a chain or rope. Two curved arms extend outwards and downwards from the base of the shank, each terminating in a sharp, triangular fluke. The overall shape is clean and well-defined, characteristic of a graphic symbol rather than a realistic depiction."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_10.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANCHOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">A white or light gray metallic anchor, centrally depicted with a classic design including a shank, stock, and flukes, set against a dark background.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_10.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BACKGROUND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">A solid, dark black rectangular area that serves as the backdrop for the white anchor.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_10.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMAGE_9&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image is a grayscale icon commonly used to represent a restroom or public toilets. It features two stylized human figures, a female and a male, standing side-by-side. The figure on the left represents a female, depicted with a triangular or bell-shaped lower body, suggesting a skirt or dress, and a circular head. The figure on the right represents a male, with a rectangular body and a circular head. Both figures are rendered as solid black silhouettes against a lighter, possibly white or light gray, background. They appear to be enclosed within a simple, slightly arched or rectangular frame, which might symbolize an entrance or a door. The overall design is minimalist and symbolic, characteristic of public signage."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_9.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEMALE FIGURE SILHOUETTE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">A stylized, black silhouette of a female figure, typically depicted with a triangular lower body suggesting a dress or skirt. This universal pictogram is commonly used on signs to represent women's facilities, such as restrooms.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_9.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MALE FIGURE SILHOUETTE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">A stylized, black silhouette of a male figure, typically depicted with a rectangular lower body suggesting trousers. This universal pictogram is commonly used on signs to represent men's facilities, such as restrooms.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_9.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESTROOM SIGN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">A common pictogram used to indicate public restrooms, featuring a dark background with two white stylized human figures side-by-side – typically a female silhouette on the left and a male silhouette on the right. In Yellowstone National Park, 'Restrooms' are explicitly listed as services available at various locations including Bridge Bay, Canyon, Fishing Bridge, Grant Village, Lake Village, Mammoth Hot Springs, Old Faithful, Roosevelt, and Tower Fall. Furthermore, picnic areas throughout the park usually provide toilets, implying the widespread presence of such signs to guide visitors to these facilities.</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_9.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMAGE_8&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image is a small, extremely low-resolution, pixelated square graphic rendered in grayscale. It features two blocky, abstract shapes that strongly resemble the letters 'FS' in a bold, sans-serif style. These shapes are depicted in various shades of light gray, appearing to have a slight gradient or embossed effect, against a dark, almost black background. The pixelation is very prominent, making the edges of the shapes jagged and indistinct. The overall impression is that of a highly stylized or severely downscaled icon or symbol, rather than a detailed photograph or illustration."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_8.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMAGE_7&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image displays a small, monochrome graphic featuring two capital letters, 'FS', rendered in a stylized, blocky, and somewhat pixelated font. The letters are depicted in a light gray or white color with subtle gradient shading, giving them a metallic or embossed appearance, suggesting depth. They are centrally positioned against a solid, dark, likely black, square background. The overall resolution of the image appears low, contributing to the pixelated quality of both the letters and the background edges. The graphic functions as a simple, abstract symbol or icon."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_7.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMAGE_6&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image displays a collection of five grayscale books or guides, likely related to national parks, arranged against a plain white background. All items are oriented vertically, with their covers facing the viewer, and are slightly overlapping, creating a sense of a casual display of literature. Starting from the top left, a small, folded brochure or map is partially visible, appearing to be white with some dark text and graphic elements, though the specific content is indistinct due to its partial view and the grayscale conversion.Below and slightly to the right of the brochure, at the bottom left, is a book or guide with a dark, possibly black or dark blue, spine and a cover featuring a landscape image. The image appears to depict mountains or a natural vista, possibly with water. Part of the title is visible, starting with letters that could be 'CRATER' or similar, in a lighter font.In the middle-left, a taller, narrower guide stands prominently. Its cover is light-colored, possibly white or light gray, and features a distinct black and white photograph of a geyser or hot spring erupting, with steam rising. The title, clearly legible, reads "YELLOWSTONE AND GRAND TETON NATIONAL PARKS Road Guide" in dark, bold lettering.Dominating the center-right and positioned slightly behind the other items is the largest book. Its cover is light gray or white, with the prominent title "YELLOWSTONE" in large, dark, sans-serif font at the top. Below this, smaller text reads "THE OFFICIAL GUIDE TO AMERICA'S FIRST NATIONAL PARK". The bottom portion of the cover features a silhouette graphic of several bison or similar large wildlife, adding to the park theme.Finally, on the far right, another book or guide is visible. Its cover is darker, possibly black or a very dark gray, and features an image of several animals, possibly elk or deer, in a natural setting. The title is partially obscured but appears to include words like 'FAUNA' or 'FLORA' and mentions 'YELLOWSTONE'.The overall arrangement suggests a selection of informational or educational materials available for national park visitors, consistent with the provided context mentioning "YellowstoneAssociation.org" for ordering."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_6.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;YELLOWSTONE: THE AMERICAN GUIDE NATIONAL PARK BOOK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A large, light-colored book or guide with the prominent title 'YELLOWSTONE' and 'THE AMERICAN GUIDE TO ITS NATIONAL PARK'. The bottom features an illustration of several bison. It appears to be a comprehensive guide to Yellowstone National Park."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_6.jpg</data>
</node>
